title: Youth struck in head with brick during out-of-control Melbourne house party
text:
Youth struck in head with brick during out-of-control Melbourne house party By 9NEWS Police arrived at the house party around 1am. (9NEWS) 
A young person has been hit in the head with a brick during an out-of-control party in Melbourne last night. 
Police said they found almost 60 people at a home on Prior Street in Malvern East about 11pm, and believe they were gate-crashing a party. 
The crowd quickly dispersed when officers arrived but three people needed medical assistance and were taken to hospital, including one person with serious injuries. A brick can be seen near the home after the out-of-control house party. (9NEWS) 
Police said they are speaking to a number of witnesses but no one has been arrested. 
Anyone with information is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000. Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
